'''Association of Nurses in AIDS Care''' (ANAC) is a national nursing organization in the United States which specializes in the care of individuals infected with [[HIV]]. It is based in [[Akron, Ohio]] and was founded in 1987.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ajc.com/hotjobs/content/hotjobs/careercenter/pulse/2007/0207_pulse0201.html |work=Atlanta Journal-Constitution |date= |title=Nurses fight the good fight against AIDS |first=Laura |last=Raines |accessdate=November 18, 2009}}</ref>
Its official journal is the ''[[Journal of the Association of Nurses in AIDS Care]]'' (JANAC), which is published on behalf of ANAC by [[Elsevier]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.infectioncontroltoday.com/hotnews/4bh210550.html |title=Association of Nurses in AIDS Care Selects Elsevier as Publishing Partner |work=Infection Control Today |date=November 2, 2004 |accessdate=November 18, 2009}}</ref>
