'''Nap pods''' are special chairs, often used in corporate/workplace environments and universities, that allow people to nap. They are available at [[JFK airport]],<ref name="MyUser_CNN_May_30_2016c">{{cite web |url=http://money.cnn.com/2016/04/19/pf/jetblue-nap-pods-jfk-airport/ |title=JetBlue now has nap pods at JFK airport - Apr. 19, 2016 |newspaper=CNN |date=  |author= |accessdate= May 30, 2016}}</ref> [[Google]], and [[Zappos]].<ref name="MyUser_Inc.com_May_30_2016c">{{cite web |url=http://www.inc.com/zoe-henry/google-uber-and-other-companies-where-you-can-nap-at-the-office.html |title=6 Companies (Including Uber) Where It's OK to Nap |newspaper=Inc.com |date=  |author= |accessdate= May 30, 2016}}</ref> [[Washington State University]] also offers some.<ref name="MyUser_The_New_York_Times_May_30_2016c">{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/04/10/education/edlife/power-napping-on-campus.html |title=Power Napping on Campus |newspaper=The New York Times |date= April 8, 2016 |author= |accessdate= May 30, 2016}}</ref>

