'''''Soul, Mind, Body Medicine: A Complete Soul Healing System for Optimum Health and Vitality''''' is a [[self-help book]] written by spiritual healer [[Zhi Gang Sha]] which provides a controversial interpretation of [[Traditional Chinese medicine]] and [[quantum physics]]. Published in 2006, within three weeks of its release the book was placed in the top five of [[The New York Times Best Seller list|''The New York Times'' Best Seller list]].<ref>{{Citation | last = Katayama  | first = Lisa  | title = Dr. Sha, a Healer With a Modern Spin: He Downloads New Organs  | work = [[Wired (magazine)|Wired]]  | publisher = Condé Nast  | date = April 5, 2007  | url = https://www.wired.com/culture/lifestyle/news/2007/04/drsha_0405  | accessdate =October 5, 2011}}</ref>

